First recall the Product Property of radicals:

√[n]{ab}=√[n]{a}·√[n]{b}, provided a,b≥0.

a) √[4]{32}

Write 32 as a product that includes a perfect 4th-power factor.
32 = 16·2 = (2⁴)·2

√[4]{32}=√[4]{2⁴·2}=√[4]{2⁴}·√[4]{2}=2·√[4]{2}

Simplified result: 2√[4]{2}

b) √[5]{64}

Write 64 as a product that includes a perfect 5th-power factor.
64 = 2⁶ = 2⁵·2

√[5]{64}=√[5]{2⁵·2}=√[5]{2⁵}·√[5]{2}=2·√[5]{2}

Simplified result: 2√[5]{2}

