a)  
\[
\sqrt{192\,q^3\,r^7}
=\sqrt{64\cdot3\;q^2\cdot q\;r^6\cdot r}
=8\,\sqrt{q^2}\,\sqrt{r^6}\,\sqrt{3\,q\,r}
=8\,|q|\,|r^3|\,\sqrt{3qr}
=8\,|q|\,|r|^3\,\sqrt{3qr}\,. 
\]

b)  
\[
\sqrt[3]{54\,m^9\,n^{10}}
=\sqrt[3]{27\cdot2\;m^{3\cdot3}\;n^{3\cdot3}\;n}
=3\,m^3\,n^3\;\sqrt[3]{2\,n}\,.
\]
(No absolute‐values are needed for an odd root.)

c)  
\[
\sqrt[4]{81\,a^9\,b^8}
=\sqrt[4]{3^4\;a^{4\cdot2}\;a\;b^{4\cdot2}}
=3\;\sqrt[4]{a^8}\;\sqrt[4]{b^8}\;\sqrt[4]{a}
=3\;|a^2|\;|b^2|\;\sqrt[4]{a}
=3\,a^2\,b^2\,\sqrt[4]{a}\,,
\]
since \(\sqrt[4]{a^8}=|a^2|\) and \(\sqrt[4]{b^8}=|b^2|,\) but \(|a^2|=a^2,\;|b^2|=b^2.\)

Here are the simplifications, using the fact that  
\(\displaystyle \sqrt[n]{\frac{a}{b}} = \frac{\sqrt[n]{a}}{\sqrt[n]{b}}\).  

a) \(\displaystyle \sqrt{\frac{45}{80}}\)  
\[
\sqrt{\frac{45}{80}}
=\frac{\sqrt{45}}{\sqrt{80}}
=\frac{3\sqrt5}{4\sqrt5}
=\frac{3}{4}.
\]

b) \(\displaystyle \sqrt[3]{\frac{8}{27}}\)  
\[
\sqrt[3]{\frac{8}{27}}
=\frac{\sqrt[3]{8}}{\sqrt[3]{27}}
=\frac{2}{3}.
\]

c) \(\displaystyle \sqrt[4]{\frac{1}{81}}\)  
\[
\sqrt[4]{\frac{1}{81}}
=\frac{\sqrt[4]{1}}{\sqrt[4]{81}}
=\frac{1}{3}
\quad(\text{since }81=3^4).
\]

